There are authorized to be appropriated to the Department of Health and Human Services to carry out this chapter—(1) $750,000,000 for fiscal year 2001;

(2) $1,000,000,000 for fiscal year 2002;

(3) $1,500,000,000 for fiscal year 2003; and

(4) such sums as may be necessary for each of the fiscal years 2004 and 2005.

(Pub. L. 106–554, § 1(a)(1) [title VIII, § 805], Dec. 21, 2000, 114 Stat. 2763, 2763A–82.)</akn:p></akn:content><akn:subsection eId="subsec_9404_1"><akn:num>(1)</akn:num><akn:content><akn:p>(1) $750,000,000 for fiscal year 2001;</akn:p></akn:content></akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_9404_2"><akn:num>(2)</akn:num><akn:content><akn:p>(2) $1,000,000,000 for fiscal year 2002;</akn:p></akn:content></akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_9404_3"><akn:num>(3)</akn:num><akn:content><akn:p>(3) $1,500,000,000 for fiscal year 2003; and</akn:p></akn:content></akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_9404_4"><akn:num>(4)</akn:num><akn:content><akn:p>(4) such sums as may be necessary for each of the fiscal years 2004 and 2005.</akn:p></akn:content></akn:subsection></akn:section></akn:body></akn:act></akn:akomaNtoso>